---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuarterCalculator from '../components/QuarterCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Quarter Calculator — Calendar & Fiscal Quarters | Clockr"
	description="Find which quarter any date falls in — calendar or UK fiscal year. See the quarter date range, days remaining and days elapsed. Free quarter calculator."
>
	<div class="qc-page">
		<div class="qc-header">
			<div class="qc-eyebrow">
				<span class="qc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				Calendar & Dates
			</div>
			<h1 class="qc-title">
				<span class="qc-gradient">Quarter</span><br />
				<span class="qc-gradient">Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="qc-subtitle">
				Find which quarter any date falls in — calendar or fiscal year
			</p>
		</div>

		<QuarterCalculator client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="qc-how">
			<h2 class="qc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="qc-how-card">
				<p>
					A calendar year is divided into four quarters of three months each.
					Q1 runs January through March, Q2 April through June, Q3 July through
					September, and Q4 October through December. Companies, investors, and
					analysts use quarterly periods to report earnings, track sales targets,
					and compare performance year on year — because three-month blocks are
					long enough to show trends but short enough to act on quickly.
				</p>
				<p>
					Not every organisation follows the calendar year. In the UK, the
					fiscal (tax) year runs from 1 April to 31 March, so Q1 is April–June,
					Q2 July–September, Q3 October–December, and Q4 January–March. Switch
					the toggle above to see fiscal quarters instead. Other countries use
					different start dates — for example, the US federal government's
					fiscal year begins on 1 October, while many US companies align with
					the calendar year.
				</p>
				<p>
					Enter any date and Clockr identifies the correct quarter, labels it
					with the relevant year, and shows the exact start and end dates of
					that quarter. The tool also counts how many days have elapsed since the
					quarter began and how many remain until it ends — useful for deadline
					planning, budget tracking, and knowing where you stand in the
					reporting cycle.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="qc-faq">
			<h2 class="qc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="qc-faq-list">
				<details class="qc-faq-item">
					<summary class="qc-faq-question"
						>What are the calendar quarters of the year?</summary
					>
					<div class="qc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							In the standard calendar year, Q1 is January–March, Q2 is
							April–June, Q3 is July–September, and Q4 is October–December.
							Each quarter covers exactly three months, though the number of
							days varies because months have different lengths and Q1 may
							include 29 February in a leap year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="qc-faq-item">
					<summary class="qc-faq-question"
						>What is the UK fiscal year and how does it differ from the calendar
						year?</summary
					>
					<div class="qc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The UK fiscal year for tax and government accounting runs from 1
							April to 31 March. Its quarters are shifted accordingly: Q1 is
							April–June, Q2 July–September, Q3 October–December, and Q4
							January–March. A date in February 2026, for instance, falls in Q4
							of the fiscal year ending 31 March 2026 — not Q1 of the calendar
							year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="qc-faq-item">
					<summary class="qc-faq-question"
						>What quarter is it right now?</summary
					>
					<div class="qc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							This page defaults to today's date, so the result updates
							automatically when you load it. Click the "Today" button in the
							quick-reference section to reset the date field, or toggle between
							calendar and fiscal year to see both interpretations.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="qc-faq-item">
					<summary class="qc-faq-question"
						>When does Q1 start in the UK tax year?</summary
					>
					<div class="qc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Q1 of the UK fiscal year begins on 1 April and ends on 30 June.
							This is the first quarter of the tax year that runs through to 31
							March of the following calendar year. For example, Q1 of fiscal
							year 2026 runs from 1 April 2025 to 30 June 2025.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="qc-faq-item">
					<summary class="qc-faq-question"
						>How many days are in each quarter?</summary
					>
					<div class="qc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Calendar Q1 has 90 days in a common year or 91 in a leap year
							(because of 29 February). Q2 always has 91 days, Q3 has 92, and
							Q4 has 92. UK fiscal quarters follow the same month groupings, so
							the day counts are identical — only the quarter labels and year
							assignments differ.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="qc-faq-item">
					<summary class="qc-faq-question"
						>Why do businesses report results by quarter?</summary
					>
					<div class="qc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Quarterly reporting gives stakeholders regular updates on company
							performance without the noise of monthly figures or the lag of
							annual reports. Regulators in many countries require listed
							companies to publish quarterly earnings. It also helps teams set
							seasonal targets, compare year-on-year growth, and align budgets
							with predictable three-month cycles.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="qc-faq-item">
					<summary class="qc-faq-question"
						>What fiscal year does the US government use?</summary
					>
					<div class="qc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The US federal government's fiscal year runs from 1 October to 30
							September. Federal Q1 is October–December, Q2 January–March, Q3
							April–June, and Q4 July–September. This differs from both the
							calendar year and the UK April–March fiscal year. Many private US
							companies still use calendar-year quarters for their own
							reporting.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="qc-related">
			<h3 class="qc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="qc-related-grid">
				<a href="/week-number-calculator" class="qc-related-card"
					><span class="qc-related-name">Week Number Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/business-days" class="qc-related-card"
					><span class="qc-related-name">Business Days Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/date-calculator" class="qc-related-card"
					><span class="qc-related-name">Date Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/day-of-week" class="qc-related-card"
					><span class="qc-related-name">Day of the Week Calculator</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.qc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.qc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.qc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.qc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.qc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.qc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.qc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.qc-mode-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.qc-mode-toggle {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.qc-mode-btn {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 12px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease,
			color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.qc-mode-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.qc-mode-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.6);
		background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.08);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.qc-input-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.qc-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
	}

	.qc-input {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		min-width: 280px;
	}

	.qc-input:focus {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
	}

	.qc-results {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.qc-main-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 40px;
		text-align: center;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.06);
	}

	.qc-quarter-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 56px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.1;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.qc-quarter-range {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 24px;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.qc-stats {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 48px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.qc-stat {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
	}

	.qc-stat-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: #fff;
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.qc-stat-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
	}

	.qc-quick {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.qc-quick-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.qc-quick-btn {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #fff;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.qc-quick-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.5);
		background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.04);
	}

	.qc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.qc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.qc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.qc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.qc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.qc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.qc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.qc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.qc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.qc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.qc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.qc-faq-item[open] .qc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.qc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.qc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.qc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.qc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.qc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.qc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.qc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4);
	}

	.qc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.qc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.qc-quarter-title {
			font-size: 40px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.qc-quick-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}

		.qc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.qc-stats {
			gap: 32px;
		}
	}
</style>
